<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-27T07:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-27T07:35:00-05:00" n="494" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d494">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/10–2744: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-27T16:00:00+03:25">October 27, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received October 27—1:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>786. Tudeh (masses) Party<note n="73" xml:id="d494fn73">Iranian
                                    Communist Party.</note> started mass demonstration today in
                                front of Majlis demanding ouster of Saed government. While crowd has
                                been estimated as high as 35,000 persons it was completely orderly
                                and though a great quantity of Iranian armed troops, tanks, et
                                cetera appeared there have been no incidents as far as Embassy is
                                aware. Some Soviet troops armed with Tommy guns were present and
                                Soviet sponsorship of the demonstration cannot be questioned.</p>
                            <p>Sent to Department repeated to Moscow.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>